(82, 1, '2015-09-18 01:16:49', '2015-09-18 01:16:49', '\r\nRoboCamps are a unique and innovative way to engage children in STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics).  RoboCamps are run by FIRST Australia, part of the largest robotics for sport organisation in the world. The camps are run professionally with fun and education at the very core of what we do.  Currently, all these camps are run out of Macquarie University, Sydney Australia\r\n\r\n \r\nLevels\r\n\r\nRoboCamps come in three different levels:\r\n\r\nBeginner: Teach the LEGO Robotic basics – for those who’ve had little to no experience with LEGO Robotics.\r\n\r\n Cost: $90 a day\r\n\r\nIntermediate: The tech wiz – for those who’ve used the NXT/EV3 Robot before, and know their stuff! Ready for a challenge? Intermediate is for you.\r\n\r\nCost: $100 a day\r\n\r\nAdvanced: Are you in high school? Are bigger, stronger, faster and funner adjectives you like the sound of? Then Advanced camps are for you. Bigger, stronger, faster and funner robots await you.\r\n\r\nCost: $120 a day\r\n\r\nCamps all run from 9:00am – 5:00pm. Drop off and registration open at 8:45am. Pickup is between 4:45 and 5:00pm.\r\nWho is teaching my Child?\r\n\r\nOur RoboCamps are run with upmost professionalism and fun. Our camps are run by Macquarie University students, or members of the Thunder Down Under robotics team. We want to make sure your child is safe and having fun at all times. With Macquarie University covering all bases, your child is in excellent hands! All 18+ camp facilitators have working with children checks and go through training to ensure they understand the right course of action, should an incident occur.\r\n\r\nWe encourage parents who have any concerns to please feel free to contact the RoboCamps coordinator – James McArthur. Mob: 0432 853 961.\r\nLocations\r\n\r\nRoboCamps are run out of Macquarie University’s Department of Engineering and FIRST Australia. These camps are located in building E6A, on the second floor. More information about rooms etc. is given upon registration; as they are subject to change throughout the year. Our facilities are held in safe, secure rooms – with bathrooms and bubblers near-by for safe and secure access. Your children are our number one priority.\r\n\r\n \r\nPayment and Registration\r\n\r\nFollow the links to register for the camps. Extra information in relation to the camp will be sent out upon registration.\r\n\r\nIf you have difficulties with registration, or do not receive a confirmation within a week of registration, please email James McArthur. You may also contact James via mobile: +61 432 853 961. Upon registration you will receive an email within two days, confirming your registration.', 'RoboCamps', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'robocamps', '', '', '2015-09-22 03:45:24', '2015-09-22 03:45:24', '', 89, 'http://localhost/firstau/?page_id=82', 0, 'page', '', 0),
